    <note>Chen(1) Gongqi [3074] Fujian TZ, 147.34b. According to Sanshan zhi, 32.37b, his descendant Yingshen [14578] (q.v.) was the great grandnephew of Jiong(2) [14528], who also received the jinshi in 1235. This would make Gongqi and his kin all members of a cadet branch of Chen Xiang's [7005] lineage and therefore Yingchuan Chen. Since Chen Wen [14554] was the only son of Jia(3) [14570] and father of Xian(3) [14266] and Xun(2) [14555], who moved to Fuzhou, I am identifying Gongqi as a lineal descendant of Wen. Other source (mis-)cited in CBD, 3, 2557.</note>
